Desting/forcing others to log off.
---------------------------------------------------------------------
 
Desting players for any reason except if its your test character
or the player is obviouly cheating and you need to dest them to
quickly prevent a major problem is strictly forbidden.  The command
is there for you to get rid of test objects or monsters, not for
you to have fun at other players expenses.  If you dest another player
for any reason except for the above exceptions, you are subject to
immediate demotion if the victim wishes it.  Demotions will be as follows.
1st offense.  1 level.
2nd offense.  10% reduction in level.
3rd offense.  You get to become a player at level 1.
4th offense.  Removal and banishment of your character.
 
Wizards and Arches desting other wizards and Arches.  Not allowed period,
unless the person asks to be dested for some reason.  Offenses of the above
rule will result in hte same punishement as above.
 
Anyone desting a higher ranked wizard is immediate grounds for demotion.
UNDER NO CIRCUMSTANCES WILL ANYONE DEST A SAGE, DEMI, OR GOD.  Infractions
to this rule will result in immediate demotion to level 102 for the first
offense level 1 for the 2nd offense.
 
SAGE, DEMI, and GOD's are exempt from above rules, unless they prove
themselves unable to use common sense.  In which case they most likey
wouldnt have given the postion in the first place.
 
